# NutriMind Flutter Skill
# Version: 1.0
# Use this skill when building the NutriMind app in Google Antigravity or Claude Code

---

## SKILL IDENTITY

name: nutrimind-flutter
description: Build the NutriMind AI food intelligence Flutter app
stack: Flutter 3.x, Dart, Gemini 2.0 Flash, Hive, Riverpod 2.x
platform: Android + iOS

---

## CONTEXT FILES TO READ FIRST

Before writing any code, read these files in this order:
1. `PRD.md` — Product requirements, features, design system
2. `TRD.md` — Technical stack, file structure, code patterns, Hive models
3. `DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md` — Phase-by-phase TODOs

---

## CODING STANDARDS

### Dart / Flutter Rules
- All files use `lowerCamelCase` for variables, `UpperCamelCase` for classes
- All screens are `ConsumerWidget` or `ConsumerStatefulWidget` (Riverpod)
- All async operations use `AsyncValue` — handle loading/error/data states
- Never use `setState` directly — always use Riverpod notifiers
- Always add `const` constructors where possible
- Use named parameters for all widget constructors with more than 2 params
- All colors from `AppColors` constants — never hardcode hex values
- All text styles from `AppTypography` constants — never hardcode fontSize

### File Naming
- screens: `home_screen.dart`, `chat_screen.dart`
- widgets: `habit_card.dart`, `message_bubble.dart`
- providers: `chat_provider.dart`
- models: `habit.dart`, `user_profile.dart`
- services: `gemini_service.dart`

### Import Order (enforce this order)
```dart
// 1. Dart SDK
import 'dart:async';
// 2. Flutter
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
// 3. Third-party packages
import 'package:flutter_riverpod/flutter_riverpod.dart';
// 4. Local imports
import 'package:nutrimind/core/constants/colors.dart';
```

---

## DESIGN RULES (NEVER VIOLATE)

- Background: ALWAYS `AppColors.surface` (#0A0A0A) — never white
- Primary action color: ALWAYS `AppColors.primary` (#1DB954 green)
- Cards: ALWAYS `AppColors.surface2` (#1A1A1A) with `borderRadius: 16`
- Padding: Use multiples of 8 — `8, 12, 16, 20, 24`
- No shadows — use subtle borders (`Color(0x20FFFFFF)`) for card separation
- All buttons: height 52, borderRadius 12, Poppins SemiBold 16
- Bottom nav: `NavigationBar` widget with `indicatorColor: AppColors.primary`

---

## ANIMATION RULES

Always use `flutter_animate` for:
- Screen elements entering: `.animate().fadeIn(duration: 400.ms).slideY(begin: 0.3)`
- Staggered lists: add `.delay(n * 100.ms)` per item
- Score circles: `Tween` animation from 0 to value, 800ms, Curves.easeOutCubic
- Button presses: scale 0.95 on tap

Never animate:
- Text content changes (just update directly)
- Loading states (use shimmer instead)

---

## GEMINI API RULES

- Model: ALWAYS `gemini-2.0-flash` — never use Pro in this app (too slow)
- Max tokens: 800 for chat, 600 for DIY checker, 200 for tips/summaries
- Temperature: 0.7 for chat, 0.3 for analysis (more deterministic)
- Always include system prompt with full user context
- Always handle errors: show snackbar, log error, don't crash
- DIY Checker response MUST start with `SCORE:XX` — parse this first
- Chat responses should NOT start with "I" — Meera speaks warmly, not formally

---

## HIVE RULES

- Open all boxes in `main.dart` before `runApp()`
- Never call `Hive.openBox` in widget build — always pre-open
- Use `box.get(key, defaultValue: ...)` — never assume key exists
- Always run `build_runner` after model changes: `flutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs`
- Box names as constants in a `HiveBoxNames` class

---

## VOICE RULES

- Always request microphone permission before first STT use
- Show visual feedback IMMEDIATELY when mic is tapped (don't wait for permission)
- Speaking: strip all markdown (`*`, `_`, `#`, `` ` ``) before passing to TTS
- Language: always `en-IN` for both STT and TTS
- Stop TTS on new user message (don't overlap)
- Voice mode state persists across the chat session but resets on app restart

---

## CONTEXT ENGINE RULES

The context string injected into every Gemini call must include:
1. User name, age, city, dietary preference, allergies, health goal
2. Active habits with current streak count
3. Last 5 meals from food_log (name + date)
4. Summary of last conversation
5. Today's habit completion count

Rebuild context on every API call — never cache it (data changes frequently)
Keep context string under 800 tokens — truncate older meals/conversations if needed

---

## ERROR HANDLING PATTERNS

```dart
// Standard async pattern for all Gemini calls
Future<void> sendMessage(String text) async {
  state = state.copyWith(isLoading: true);
  try {
    final response = await _geminiService.sendMessage(...);
    // handle success
  } on DioException catch (e) {
    _showError('Connection error. Check your internet.');
  } catch (e) {
    _showError('Something went wrong. Try again.');
  } finally {
    state = state.copyWith(isLoading: false);
  }
}
```

---

## WHAT NOT TO BUILD

- No authentication / login screens
- No server-side API calls except Gemini
- No camera / photo scanning (not in scope)
- No push notifications (too complex for demo)
- No social features
- No payment screens
- No calorie counting (qualitative only, not quantitative)
- No external nutrition database API calls

---

